tr: the side that goes last or is not normally seen
example: he wrote the date on the back of the photograph

tr: the fleshy part of the human body that you sit on
example: he deserves a good kick in the butt
are you going to sit on your fanny and do nothing?

tr: the back of a military formation or procession
the part of something that is furthest from the normal viewer
example: he stood at the back of the stage
it was hidden in the rear of the store

tr: the side of an object that is opposite its front
example: his room was toward the rear of the hotel

tr: stand up on the hind legs, of quadrupeds

value.def: The rear of something such as a building or vehicle is the back part of it.

example.ex: He settled back in the rear of the taxi.
example.tran: 他靠坐在出租车的后排座上。

example.ex: ...a stairway in the rear of the building.
Manufacturers have been obliged to fit rear seat belts in all new cars.
example.tran: 生产商们不得不在所有新车的后排座椅上安装安全带。

value.tran: （建筑物或车辆的）后部，后面，背面

value.def: If you are at the rear of a moving line of people, you are the last person in it.

example.ex: Musicians played at the front and rear of the procession...
example.tran: 乐师们在队前和队尾表演。

example.ex: The Lord Mayor follows at the rear in his gilded coach.
example.tran: 市长大人坐在他阔气的马车里在后面跟着。

value.def: Your rear is the part of your body that you sit on.

example.ex: I turned away from the phone to see Lewis pat a waitress on her rear.
example.tran: 我打完电话后转过头，看见刘易斯拍了拍一个女招待的屁股。

value.def: If you rear children, you look after them until they are old enough to look after themselves.

example.ex: She reared sixteen children, six her own and ten her husband's...
example.tran: 她养大了16个孩子，其中6个是她亲生的，10个是她丈夫带来的。

example.ex: I was reared in east Texas.
example.tran: 我在得克萨斯州东部长大。

value.def: If you rear a young animal, you keep and look after it until it is old enough to be used for work or food, or until it can look after itself.

example.ex: She spends a lot of time rearing animals.
example.tran: 她花费大量时间饲养动物。

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 raise

value.def: When a horse rears, it moves the front part of its body upwards, so that its front legs are high in the air and it is standing on its back legs.

example.ex: The horse reared and threw off its rider.
example.tran: 那匹马前蹄腾空向后仰，把骑手摔了下去。

example.ex: ...an army pony that didn't rear up at the sound of gunfire.
example.tran: 听到枪声不会仰站立起的军用小型马

value.def: If you say that something such as a building or mountain rears above you, you mean that is very tall and close to you.

example.ex: The exhibition hall reared above me behind a high fence...
example.tran: 高高的围墙后面，展览大厅耸立在我面前。

example.ex: The mountains reared up on each side, steep and white.
example.tran: 两边的山峦高耸入云，山势陡峭，覆盖着积雪。

value.def: If a person or vehicle is bringing up the rear, they are the last person or vehicle in a moving line of them.

example.ex: ...police motorcyclists bringing up the rear of the procession.
example.tran: 摩托骑警行进在队伍最后

value.def: If something unpleasant rears its head or rears its ugly head, it becomes visible or noticeable.

example.ex: The threat of strikes reared its head again this summer...
example.tran: 今年夏天又显现出了罢工的势头。

example.ex: The extreme right reared its ugly head in the 1980s.
example.tran: 极右势力在20世纪80年代有所抬头。

value.tran: （令人不快之物）显现，露头，显露

trans: 保护自己(免受批评、谴责等);辩解
